==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fuddle
<hw>Fud"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Fuddled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fuddling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Perh. formed as a
kind of dim. of full. Cf. <er>Fuzzle</er>.]</ety> <def>To make foolish
by drink; to cause to become intoxicated.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am too <qex>fuddled</qex> to take care to observe your
orders.</q> <rj><qau>Steele.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fuddle</ent>⟦br⟧

